#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn52.2"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn52.2:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 52 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 52 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn52.2:0.2"
msgid "1. Rahogatavagga "
msgstr "1. In Private "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn52.2:0.3"
msgid "2. Dutiyarahogatasutta "
msgstr "2. In Private (2nd) "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn52.2:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn52.2:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmato anuruddhassa rahogatassa paṭisallīnassa evaṃ cetaso parivitakko udapādi: "
msgstr "Then as Anuruddha was in private retreat this thought came to his mind: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn52.2:1.3"
msgid "“yesaṃ kesañci cattāro satipaṭṭhānā viraddhā, viraddho tesaṃ ariyo maggo sammā dukkhakkhayagāmī; "
msgstr "“Whoever has missed out on these four kinds of mindfulness meditation has missed out on the noble path to the complete ending of suffering. "

msgctxt "sn52.2:1.4"
msgid "yesaṃ kesañci cattāro satipaṭṭhānā āraddhā, āraddho tesaṃ ariyo maggo sammā dukkhakkhayagāmī”ti. "
msgstr "Whoever has undertaken these four kinds of mindfulness meditation has undertaken the noble path to the complete ending of suffering.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.297, sc2, sc3
msgctxt "sn52.2:2.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā mahāmoggallāno āyasmato anuruddhassa cetasā cetoparivitakkamaññāya—seyyathāpi nāma balavā puriso samiñjitaṃ vā bāhaṃ pasāreyya, pasāritaṃ vā bāhaṃ samiñjeyya; evameva—āyasmato anuruddhassa sammukhe pāturahosi. Atha kho āyasmā mahāmoggallāno āyasmantaṃ anuruddhaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then Venerable Mahāmoggallāna knew what Venerable Anuruddha was thinking. As easily as a strong person would extend or contract their arm, he reappeared in front of Anuruddha and said to him: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn52.2:2.2"
msgid "“kittāvatā nu kho, āvuso anuruddha, bhikkhuno cattāro satipaṭṭhānā āraddhā hontī”ti? "
msgstr "“Reverend Anuruddha, how do you define the undertaking of the four kinds of mindfulness meditation by a mendicant?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn52.2:4.1"
msgid "“Idhāvuso, bhikkhu ajjhattaṃ kāye kāyānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ. "
msgstr "“Reverend, it’s when a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the body internally—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world. "

msgctxt "sn52.2:4.2"
msgid "Bahiddhā kāye kāyānupassī viharati … pe … "
msgstr "They meditate observing an aspect of the body externally … "

msgctxt "sn52.2:4.3"
msgid "ajjhattabahiddhā kāye kāyānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ. "
msgstr "internally and externally—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn52.2:5.1"
msgid "Ajjhattaṃ vedanāsu vedanānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ. "
msgstr "They meditate observing an aspect of feelings internally … "

msgctxt "sn52.2:5.2"
msgid "Bahiddhā vedanāsu vedanānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ. "
msgstr "externally … "

msgctxt "sn52.2:5.3"
msgid "Ajjhattabahiddhā vedanāsu vedanānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ. "
msgstr "internally and externally … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn52.2:6.1"
msgid "Ajjhattaṃ citte … pe … "
msgstr "They meditate observing an aspect of the mind internally … "

msgctxt "sn52.2:6.2"
msgid "bahiddhā citte … pe … "
msgstr "externally … "

msgctxt "sn52.2:6.3"
msgid "ajjhattabahiddhā citte cittānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ. "
msgstr "internally and externally … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "sn52.2:7.1"
msgid "Ajjhattaṃ dhammesu … pe … "
msgstr "They meditate observing an aspect of principles internally … "

msgctxt "sn52.2:7.2"
msgid "bahiddhā dhammesu … pe … "
msgstr "externally … "

msgctxt "sn52.2:7.3"
msgid "ajjhattabahiddhā dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ. "
msgstr "internally and externally—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world. "

msgctxt "sn52.2:7.4"
msgid "Ettāvatā kho, āvuso, bhikkhuno cattāro satipaṭṭhānā āraddhā hontī”ti. "
msgstr "That’s how to define the undertaking of the four kinds of mindfulness meditation by a mendicant.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn52.2:7.5"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
